  JOHANNESBURG - The police have arrested a Community Police Forum member and his son-in-law in Lenasia, south of Johannesburg. eNCA understands that a large sum of cash, allegedly ransom money from kidnappings, has been seized. The son in law is allegedly part of a syndicate led by suspected kingpin Faizal Charloos, arrested ten days ago. He and his co-accused face charges of kidnapping and illegal arms possession. READ: Alleged kidnapping kingpin arrested in Gauteng Police seized eight vehicles, including one fitted with blue lights. Charloos appeared in a Soweto court on Monday, and the bail hearing was moved to next Tuesday. A total of nine suspects are now behind parts, and more arrests are expected.  